\subsection*{Translation}

Sa\~{}njaya said: To him (Arjuna), thus, filled with compassion, with
an eye full of tears, uneasy, grieving, this group of words was said
by Madhu-destroyer (K.r.s.na): \dots
% ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
\subsection*{Notes}

\begin{itemize}

\item Verb: {\dn vad} = vad = to say.

  Plus past tense and third person form and singular form:

  {\dn uvaaca} = uvaaca = (he/she/it) said.

\item Male pronoun: {\dn sa.h} = sa.h = he/it.

  Plus \accusativecase: {\dn tam} = tam = to him/it.

\item Female noun: {\dn k.rpaa} = k.rpaa = compassion.

  Plus \instrumentalcase: {\dn k.rpayaa} = k.rpayaa = using/by compassion.

\item Adjective: {\dn aavi.s.ta} = aavi.s.ta = filled.

\item Neuter noun: {\dn a"srum} = a"srum = tear.

\item Adjective: {\dn puur.na} = puur.na = full.

\item Neuter noun: {\dn iik.sa.nam} = iik.sa.nam = eye.

\item Neuter noun: {\dn vi.saadanam} = vi.saadanam = grief.

  (?) Plus change: {\dn vi.siidantam} = vi.siidantam = causing grief.

\item Neuter noun: {\dn vaakyam} = vaakyam = group of words.

\item Male noun: {\dn madhusuudana.h} = madhusuudana.h = K.r.s.na.

  K.r.s.na killed a demon named Madhu (``honey'').

  Neuter noun: {\dn madhum} = madhum = honey.

  Neuter noun: {\dn suudanam} = suudanam = destruction.

  (?) Plus change: {\dn suudana.h} = suudana.h = destroyer.
\end{itemize}
