\subsection*{Translation}

God (K.r.s.na) said: From where, to you, comes this dirtiness, in
distress? This dirtiness is near a bad person, is not leading to
heaven, and is non-fame action, O Arjuna.
% ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
\subsection*{Notes}

\begin{itemize}

\item Neuter noun: {\dn bhagavaan} = bhagavaan = God.

\item Verb: {\dn vad} = vad = to say.

  Plus past tense and third person form and singular form:

  {\dn uvaaca} = uvaaca = (he/she/it) said.

\item Pronoun in second person form and singular form: {\dn tvam} = tvam = you.

  Plus \accusativecase: {\dn tvaam} = tvaam = to you.

  Or: {\dn tvaa} = tvaa = to you.

\item Neuter noun: {\dn ka"smalam} = ka"smalam = dirtiness.

\item Neuter noun: {\dn vi.samam} = vi.samam = distress.

  Plus \locativecase: {\dn vi.same} = vi.same = in distress.

\item Adjective: {\dn samupasthita} = samupasthita = near.

  (?) Plus change: {\dn samupasthitam} = samupasthitam = near.

\item Male noun: {\dn anaarya.h} = anaarya.h = bad person.

  (Prefix: {\dn an} = an = not.)

  (Male noun: {\dn aarya.h} = aarya.h = Aryan.)

\item Adjective: {\dn ju.s.ta} = ju.s.ta = having.

  (?) Plus change: {\dn ju.s.tam} = ju.s.tam = having.

\item Adjective: {\dn asvargya} = asvargya = not leading to heaven.

  (?) Plus change: {\dn asvargyam} = asvargyam = not leading to heaven.

\item Female noun: {\dn akiirti.h} = akiirti.h = non-fame.

  (Prefix: {\dn a} = a = not.)

  (Female noun: {\dn kiirti.h} = kiirti.h = fame.)

\item Male noun: {\dn kara.h} = kara.h = action.

  (?) Plus change: {\dn karam} = karam = action.

\item Male noun: {\dn arjuna.h} = arjuna.h = Arjuna.

  Plus \vocativecase: {\dn arjuna} = arjuna = O Arjuna.

\end{itemize}
