\subsection*{Translation}

(K.r.s.na said:) Weakness is not certainly in travel, O Arjuna. This
does not happen in you. A small heart weakness---having abandoned it,
get up, O wounder of enemies.
% ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
\subsection*{Notes}

\begin{itemize}

\item Neuter noun: {\dn klaibyam} = klaibyam = weakness.

\item Male noun: {\dn gama.h} = gama.h = travel.

\item Male noun: {\dn paartha.h} = paartha.h = P.rthaa's son = Arjuna.

  Plus \vocativecase: {\dn paartha} = paartha = O P.rthaa's son = O Arjuna.

\item Neuter pronoun: {\dn etat} = etat = this.

\item Pronoun in second person form and singular form: {\dn tvam} = tvam = you.

  Plus \locativecase: {\dn tvayi} = tvayi = in you.

\item Verb: {\dn upapad} = upapad = to happen.

  Plus present tense and third person form and singular form:

  {\dn upapadyate} = upapadyate = (he/she/it) happens.

\item Adjective: {\dn k.sudra} = k.sudra = small.

  Plus \accusativecase: {\dn k.sudram} = k.sudram = small.

\item Neuter noun: {\dn h.rdayam} = h.rdayam = heart.

\item Neuter noun: {\dn daurbalyam} = daurbalyam = weakness.

\item Verb: {\dn tyaj} = tyaj = to abandon.

  Plus present perfect participle: {\dn tyaktvaa} = tyaktvaa = having abandoned.

\item Verb: {\dn udsthaa} = udsthaa = to get up.

  Plus imperative tense and singular form: {\dn utti.s.thatu} = utti.s.thatu = get up.

\item Male noun: {\dn para.mtapa.h} = para.mtapa.h = wounder of enemies.

  Plus \vocativecase: {\dn para.mtapa} = para.mtapa = O wounder of enemies.

\end{itemize}
